What Are the Most Important Things Students Should Learn in School?

In your opinion, what are the most important things students should learn in school? What is the most important thing you have learned in school? How has this knowledge affected your life? How do you think it will help your success in the future?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the most important things students should learn in school

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This will allow for them to grow socially so they have a chance of being successful in whatever profession they are interested in pursuing.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If they are not able to get along with others, then that same ability will be lacking when out in the real world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This, in turn, will make it harder for them to be successful in whatever they are trying to do.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I do not want to sound mean, but I have seen too much abuse to kids by parents that think they can teach better than the schools.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A parent can not replace a teacher.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Therefore, your child might end up not being ok with others.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So, I do not think homeschooling is okay because it destroys your so-called social life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: follow the rules set by their workplace.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The school will allow your child to experience what its like to follow rules everyday like how it should be done in the real world.

actions.text: the most important things students should learn in school is how to interact and get along with their peers.
